Help Lightning - Android

== INTRODUCTION ==

Help Lightning is an Android application developed by Vipaar for
allowing people in remote applications to work on problems together in
real time in a mixed reality environment.

== BUILDING ==

To build Help Lightning on the command line, use:

(Development version)

To compile:
./gradlew assembleDevelopmentDebug

To install on a device or emulator:
./gradlew installDevelopmentDebug

(Production version)

To compile:
./gradlew assembleProductionRelease

To install on a device or emulator:
./gradlew installProductionRelease


You can also open this project directly in Android Studio and build
that way.

== Running Tests ==

Several unit tests are included. To run the tests, use:

./gradlew testRoboelectricDebug

Then, in a webbrowser open:

./app/build/reports/tests/roboelectricDebug/index.html

It is possible to run the unit tests through Android Studio too, by
selecting the Roboelectric build variant.

